-------------------------- Service ----------------------------

. So we have created the pod, namespace and their deployments but how can the external world access to the pod.
. In Kubernetes, a Service is a method for exposing a network application that is running as one or more Pods in your cluster.


-->> Nginx port : 80 --->>> bind to Load Balancer --->>> where user comes 


There are three type of services :- 
1. Cluster IP
2. NodePort
3. LoadBalancer
4. ExternalName 

-------------------------- Manifest file ------------------------- 

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
    name: nginx-service
    namespace: nginx
    labels:  // -->> Deployment will be identify using this label 
        app: nginx

spec:
    type: LoadBalancer
    selector: // -->> Deployment will be identify using this label
        app: nginx
    ports:
        - protocol: TCP
          port: 80 // -->> Your service port means when u enter the url www.google. 
                      com:80
          targetPort: 80  // -->> Your container port, Traffic is forwarded to:
                            PodIP:80 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------- Important Commands -------------------

- We can also check that service is accessible via
. kubectl get service -n nginx

- If want to spin up the all manifest file via one command
. kubectl apply -f .

- How to delete the cluster resources before deleting the cluster in one command 
. kubectl delete -f .

- Delete the whole cluster in one command after deleting their resoruces 
. eksctl delete cluster --name=aws-eks-learning-session --region=ap-south-1

